  "texts": [
    "Deep learning models, especially transformer-based architectures, require substantial processing power and memory, which can limit their use in resource-constrained environments like edge devices or remote locations.",
    "This constraint poses difficulties for widespread adoption and real-time application in sectors such as healthcare and IoT (Gill et al., 2024).",
    "Solution: Advances in Edge AI and model optimization techniques can help overcome these limitations.",
    "Edge AI enables data to be processed locally on devices, reducing latency and minimizing the need for constant connectivity to cloud servers.",
    "Techniques like model compression, including quantization and pruning, can decrease the model size and energy consumption, making NLP systems more viable on devices with limited resources (Gill et al., 2024)."
  ],
